Executive Profile
David   Van Skilling  Non-Executive Chairman , Onvia, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships83$50,274
Background

		Mr. David Van Skilling has been the President at Skilling Enterprises since March 1999. Mr. Van Skilling has been Private Investor since 1999. He served as the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of Experian Information Solutions Inc. (formerly TRW Information Systems & Services) from September 1996 to April 1999. Mr. Van Skilling has over 30 years experience in technological corporations. He served as an Executive Vice President of TRW Information Systems ... and Services from March 1970 to September 1996. Mr. Van Skilling has been Non Executive Chairman of Onvia Inc(also known as Onvia .Com Inc.) since November 9, 2010. He serves as the Chairman of the Board of Trustees at Colorado College. He served as the Chairman of CoreLogic, Inc. until July 29, 2014. He has been an Independent Director of Onvia Inc. since November 19, 2004. Mr. Van Skilling is a Director at The Lamson & Sessions Co. since 1989. He serves as a Director First Advantage Recruiting Solutions and American Business Bank. He served as Lead Director of First American Corporation. (formerly CoreLogic, Inc.) and served as its Director since 1998. He served as a Director of CoreLogic, Inc. until July 29, 2014. He served as a Director of Parchment Inc., He served as a Director of First Advantage Corporation since November 2005 and McDATA Corporation since May 1998. He served as a Director of Experian Information Solutions Inc. Mr. Van Skilling received his Bachelor of Science Degree in Chemistry and Zoology and BA Degree from Colorado College and his Master of Business Administration Degree in International Business from Pepperdine University in Los Angeles.Read Full Background




